				<td colspan="2"><span>Thanks again for all the information! I purchased Boastful Bellow last night and started pulling with it. I really like the instant tag, it just takes some getting used to. It was really handy when pulling through where I knew a mob would spawn at any second. I didn't risk getting whacked by being too close.
<br />

<br />
Formerly, I always pulled with snare. This gave me enough time to get back to the group, get my group songs up, and the tank had time to get aggro before I got hit. BB brings the mobs quicker but I get hit a few times before the tank takes over. Guess I better get back to working on taking a beating!! ;)
<br />

<br />
My goals are to increase mana regen (for fading and charm kiting), increase my ability to take/avoid a beating, increase the amount of damage I can do with chants. 
<br />

<br />
One more question, however not entirely related. I have all my songs made into hotkeys (typical /stopcast /cast 1). This means I have 8 keys full of songs, leaving me one key for FM, and one key that I switch out for an INC message, assist key, or a pet button. Now that I've added BB to the mix, I'm out of places for hotkeys! I hate to SHIFT 2, hit 3, SHIFT 1. Mostly because it's too many steps and I often forget to get back to my main keysheet. How do others handle this?
<br />

<br />
The first thing I did was try to make a hotkey:
<br />

<br />
/g Incoming! %T
<br />
/alt activate 199
<br />

<br />
But I found that if I didn't see my target, I had to hit the key again, thus giving 2 INC message which can be confusing.
<br />

<br />
So just curious about how others do this.</span></td>
