				<td colspan="2"><span>I use the kind of UI that lets you have 10 slots with your inventory right next to it.  Attack and fade for the first row, followed by 8 songs.  I mash the hotbottons under attack to twist and right next to it is the primary, secondary hand, with 8 inventory slots under those.  Instrument swapping is right there from inventory to primary, and the hotkeyed song bubbles are next to the inventory.  Very small mouse manouvers and double clicks on the buttons.  The only time I have to really move the mouse is to target if needed, then back to the twist area of the UI.
<br />

<br />
My command portion is just used for messages and commands.  There are quite a few pages to use up.  I have one page for instant small talk when too busy to type.  Another for commands to get around ldon, WoW.  One is for abilities, like sneak, hide, corpse, ...whatever else.  Incoming message..although I am really a bad bard when it comes to incomming messages...I just bring them solo or bring them and mez them just outside group.  If we are the cc why announce to yourself how many?  LOL just make sure they are in your total control....if you need assistance anounce.   
<br />

<br />
It is an old modified version of Kiez.  Kiez we need an extra song slot btw...9 songs vs 8 is making me have to leave one out of the hotkeys. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
